 discusses in detail the proportional changes underlying the revolutionary style instituted during the Amarna Period. She also considers how the grid system influenced the composition of scenes as a whole. Numerous line drawings with superimposed grids illustrate the text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aArt, Ancient -- Egypt. 0aArt, AncientzEgypt. 0aArt, Egyptian. 0aComposition (Art). 0aProportion (Art). 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh1 aFowler, Ann S.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292755444423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292755444/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK